          <h1 id="headingone">Ruby Hoursetheif Canyon</h1>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  <!-- Introduction -->
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col">
          <p id="intro">During the winter of 2017, a small group of us started
          looking into floating the Ruby Horsethief section of the Colorado
          River. Being that this was so far in advanced it was simply a small
          idea and the group wasn't sure if it would actaully happen. After a
          little bit of research and planning we were on our way for a 3 day
          weekend on the river.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Intro and Planning -->
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col">
            <p>One of the decisions that had to be made while planning was how
            we wanted to make the trip. Do we drive all the way to the float
            on Friday morning, or do we split the camp up into several days.
            From Denver the drive is roughly 4.5 hours, which made an easy decision.
            Let's break the trip up into an extra night and sleep a little closer
            to Loma. The first night led to a late night camp in Dillon, CO.
            We arrived in Dillon right around 8pm excited and hungry. While we were
            excited to get to camp and get the trip started we were also looking
            forward to being on a mini vacation. No better time for a beer at
            the Dam Brewery. After feeling completely clueless we figured we'd wrap
            the evening up and head to camp. The next morning brought beautiful views
            and even more excitement. With a fast clean up of camp we were on the
            road toward Loma, CO. </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>


    <div class="container">
      <img src="Small Images/1.jpg" class="img-fluid" alt="Group at Mee Corner">
    </div>


  <!-- Night One -->
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col">
        </br><p>With the help of a little permit snafoo we were able to enjoy
          the town of Grand Junction a little bit. After we enjoyed our time at
          the Mesa Community Library we hit the road, made a short pitstop at
          the Colorado/Utah border, then raced back to the Loma Boat Launch
          for some fun in the sun.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

