    <!-- Day Two -->
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col">
        <p>The second day of the river brought a completely different vibe
        than the first day did. Since we did not have anywhere to be we thought
        we would sleep in and start the day slow. And with only a couple of
        miles of paddling that is exactly what we did. After only about an hour
        we were already to our second camp spot, Black Rocks 5. With deep waters
        and high rocks this is an adventurers dream. As we floated into our spot
        we realized we were in for a hot day, and we were right. With the sun
        beating down on us all day we needed to find a way to get into some shade.
        Luckily we were able to rig up a little shade to beat the heat While
        we took breaks from being in the water. With the cliffs so close to our
        spot we couldn't help but give it a shot. After a few minutes of building
        up the courage we were ready for the plunge.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

